@tqchen

@AlecWong Seems like a simple regression problem? MXNet supports this kind of data/label combination. To get full customization, you can
1: define your own data iterator to handle such kinds of data. 
2: use lower level forward/backward APIs provided in `mx.mod.Module`

@sxjscience Yes, it can be regarded as a simple regression problem.   Could you be a bit more specific about  

>  "MXNet supports this kind of data/label combination"

?

@tqchen, Yes, we can do that. 
The current `sum_axis` only supports reducing over a single axis (or reducing over the whole tensor if axis =-1). In order to support multi-axis, I've combined multiple `sum_axis`s in the python side to construct the `sum` operator. 
It would be better to have a `sum` operator in C++ that can reduce/broadcast over multiple axes. I'll work on that.
